  "course_description": "This three-hour course will examine the employment relationship from entry through exit with a focus on Common Law principles used by many states and some background federal rules. We will examine topics including worker classification doctrine, the origins and mechanics of at-will employment, privacy at work, contract adjustment, post-employment restraints, and defamation. These foundational concepts provide the basis for more specialized issues and statutory regimes covered in other classes.",
  "course_notes": "Final Assessment: Scheduled Exam This course is eligible to be counted towards the requirements for the J.D. concentration in Health Law or Civil Litigation and Dispute Resolution.",
